// Man page for app
manApp="APP(1)                           X Shell Manual                           APP(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    app - Smart appliance interface
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>app -o</b><b> POWER TEMPERATURE</b>
    <b>app -m</b>
    <b>app -a</b><b> ACTION</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    The app utility provides a communication interface for controlling smart
    appliances. It enables power and temperature overrides, model information
    retrieval, and alarm control for connected appliances.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>-o POWER TEMPERATURE</b> - Override Settings
      Override power and temperature settings of connected appliance.
      Defaults: POWER=500, TEMPERATURE=50 (if parameters omitted)

    <b>-m</b> - View Model
      Display appliance model information.

    <b>-a ACTION</b> - Control Alarm
      Activate or deactivate malfunction sound alarm.
      Valid actions: on|off, true|false, 1|0
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Override Settings</color>
    <b>app -o 1000 75</b>
    Set power to 1000 and temperature to 75

    <b>app -o</b>
    Use default values (power: 500, temp: 50)

    <color=#e4ff34># Appliance Information</color>
    <b>app -m</b>
    Display appliance model

    <color=#e4ff34># Alarm Control</color>
    <b>app -a on</b>
    Enable malfunction alarm

    <b>app -a off</b>
    Disable malfunction alarm

    <b>app -a 1</b>
    Enable alarm using numeric value"